Class TunnelService

      com.sonyericsson.extras.liveware.extension.util.TunnelService
All Implemented Interfaces:
ExtensionService.ExtensionIntentSender
public class TunnelService
extends Service
implements ExtensionService.ExtensionIntentSender

This service enables host apps to tunnel intents through a Messenger instead of sending them over the BroadcastQueue to prevent them from being delayed by the new queue behavior in KitKat. It implements the SmartExtension Tunnel protocol. The service maintains a map of Messenger-instances. The Messenger-instances are set right after the connection has been established. They are cleared if the extension service has disconnected itself (stopSelf) or the last host app disconnects. The service can be enabled by adding it to the manifest as follows:
